Reasoning: The paper proposes a congestion control protocol for wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of feedback and optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed protocol using simulations and experiments, which could fall under cs.COMM (Computer Communication Networks) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
